urlhtml: Shoreditch Tabernacle Baptist Church & The Tab Centre
title: Shoreditch Tabernacle Baptist Church & The Tab Centre
description:
Shoreditch Tabernacle Baptist Church: The Tab in Shoreditch comprises both the church and the centre. The faith community of the church has long been involved with social action in Shoreditch and the surrounding area, and continues to be so mainly through the running of the Tab Centre. The first Tab church was founded in 1835 on the current site but in a Georgian building. From 1880-1890’s the church extended its work building a new Victorian church and church school to the rear of the building. After suffering bomb damage in the Second World War the current church building replaced the Victorian church. In 2004-5 major redevelopment restored the church school to its current standard.

The Tab Centre: The Tab Centre was built as a church school in 1890 by the Shoreditch Tabernacle Baptist Church, under the ministry of the Rev'd William Cuff. When completed, men, women and children from the East End filled the halls for school, brigades and public meetings. They were in turn entertained and scandalised by Lady Astor and Fresh Air Committee meetings.
